<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-07-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-07-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="182" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d182">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/5863</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Rumania</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_AWW1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Andrews</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jassy</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-07-06">
                                        <hi rend="italic">July 6, 1917</hi></date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received July 17, 4.32 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>90. General <persName>Scott</persName><note n="2" xml:id="d182fn2">Maj. Gen. <persName>Hugh L. Scott</persName>, of the special
                                    mission to Russia; see <ref target="frus1918Russiav01#pg_109">
                                        <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1918, Russia, Vol.
                                        I, p. 109</ref>.</note> accompanied by four officers of his
                                staff arrived on official visit Jassy July 3 leaving same night.
                                Their visit was great success and they were accorded appreciative
                                reception by Roumanian Parliament and their Majesties the King and
                                Queen. General <persName>Scott</persName>’s speech made to the
                                assembled Roumanian Parliament was greatly appreciated. He
                                reaffirmed the reasons of America’s entry into war and America’s
                                intention of aiding so far as possible the victory of the Allies
                                including Roumania.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_AWW1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Andrews</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>